cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.SE, cs.CY

The paper discusses the properties and capabilities of Blockchain technology, as well as its potential applications and how it relates to other distributed technologies. This suggests that it could fit into several sub-categories, including cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DB (Databases), cs.SE (Software Engineering), and cs.CY (Computers and Society). However, given the focus on security and distributed computing, cs.CR and cs.DC are the most likely sub-categories.
